      <notesStmt>
        <note>This text consists of expositions on two mantras,Śarabhamahāmantra (ff. 1r-2v, title from f. 1r), and Mālāmantra or Śarabhaśālava[/sāluva]pakṣirājamālāmantra (ff. 2v-7v, titles from colophon and f. 2v, respectively).</note>
        <note>Written 7-8 lines per leaf on country paper.</note>
        <note>Good condition. Water damage affecting one corner of most leaves. Mistakes crossed out or blotched out with black.</note>
        <note>Begins: śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ atha śarabhamahāmaṁtraprāraṁbhaḥ om̐ asya śrīśarabhaśālava pakṣirājamahāmaṁtrasya kālāgnirudra raṣiḥ jagatī chaṁdaḥ bhagavān śarabheśvaro devatā svaṁ vij̄aṁ svāhā śaktiḥ haṁ phaṭa kīlakaṁ</note>
        <note>Text ends (f. 7v): akhilabrahmāṁḍanāyakāya sarvajanarakṣāya 2 om̐ om̐ om̐ om̐ om̐ hrāṁ hrīṁ hrūṁ hraiṁ hrauṁ hraḥ huṁ phaṭa svāhaḥ</note>
      </notesStmt>
